entry.name: Label-free mass spectrometry-based profiling of urinary proteins and metabolites for non-invasive diagnosis of idiopathic nephrotic syndrome in children
entry.description: To identify specific urinary proteomics and metabolomics patterns associated with paediatric idiopathic nephrotic syndrome (INS).

additional_fields.field: For proteomics analysis, urine proteins were reduced and alkylated, followed by incubating with anti-HSA resin. The supernatants were collected and proteolytic digestion initiated, and qualitative and quantitative label-free LC-MS analyses conducted. For the metabolomics analysis, urine samples were purified using solid phase extraction. The resultant eluent solutions were evaporated to dryness and reconstituted prior to LC-MS analysis.

ProteinLynx GlobalSERVER v2.5.2 was used to process proteomics LC-IM-DIA-MS data. Alignment, normalization and label-free quantification were conducted with Progenesis LC-MS v4.0. The metabolomics LC-MS data were aligned and normalized using CoMet v2.0 . EZinfo v2.0 was use for multivariate statistics and metabolite identification.

Sedic M, Gethings LA, Vissers JP, Shockcor JP, McDonald S, Vasieva O, Lemac M, Langridge JI, Batinić D, Kraljević Pavelić S. Label-free mass spectrometric profiling of urinary proteins and metabolites from paediatric idiopathic nephrotic syndrome. Biochem Biophys Res Commun. 2014 Aug 20. pii: S0006-291X(14)01422-3
Department of Biotechnology, Laboratory for genomics and systems biomedicine University of Rijeka
